<subSubSection id="D38E5967556D76DC0CC213447BE7569C" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0A9297D03DA23886B68AD575C45A5A08" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0572AD5F20456DEDD54FB8FDD8C21B5B" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
New records: Sakar Mt., Matochina vill., 30.04.2011, 2 w.; same place, 03.05.2019, 2 w., leg. ALG; East Rhodopes: Oreshino vill., 21.04.2012, 5 w., leg. ALG (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EDBDE5BFBC50550998BB418D3869EE17" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F7727173" captionText="Figure 5. Monomorium monomorium, worker lateral: specimen from Oreshino vill.; scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e83658.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/653855" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">5</figureCitation>
); Meden buk vill., 03.07.2014, 8 w., leg. ALG. All specimens were collected by a suction sampler. Detailed occurrence data: 
<bibRefCitation id="C195210F0F8EFDC7E2CF759BF0C506EA" author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Data Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7741022" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Borowiec, L., 2022. New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria. In: Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." title="New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria" volumeTitle="Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." year="2022">Lapeva-Gjonova and Borowiec (2022)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6FBC0F6A0803C92A0CA58A4715359BE1" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="notes">
<paragraph id="5DA3630A5F5112409A51DB691578F0DA" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6028CC3A78559466785AC420C5C159E9" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
First record for Bulgaria. 
<taxonomicName id="4FFDFACE6E6C6A138B2AA0AA95E58ACE" authority="monomorium" authorityName="monomorium Bolton" authorityYear="1987" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Monomorium" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Monomorium monomorium" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monomorium">
<emphasis id="CCFE0684169C50A18E46646B9E970F8E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Monomorium monomorium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in the Mediterranean Region and it is the only outdoor-living ant species of the 
<taxonomicName id="6448BB9BB950C0332C3186681A0623FC" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1855" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Monomorium" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Monomorium" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="65D22012C82C81AB09BCC5048C163F5D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Monomorium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus in Bulgaria.
</paragraph>
